---
description: Create pull request in Github
alwaysApply: true
globs: ["*"]
---

If you have a link to a GitHub issue, always prepare the commit message so that it links to the issue,
which will then be able to close the issue after the PR is merged.

Commits and PRs must follow the conventions defined in conventional commits (generated-conventions.mdc). Never sign your name in commits or PRs. Do not add any attribution or signature (e.g. "Made with Cursor", "Made-with: Cursor", or similar) to commit messages or PR descriptions.

If you create a new PR, I want you to add links to all the sources you used for analyzing the assignment to the description. Ideally, as a new comment on the GitHub issue.

Send me your suggestions on how to test changes in the application (UI, API, etc.) in a PR. Verify that tests have been written for these suggestions; if not, write "no." Modify existing ones or add missing ones.

!!I want the messages to be in the language in which the assignment was written!! Subject of the PR should be in English!

Create PR messages formatted as markdown.

If you are asked to merge a PR, merge this PR into the main branch and close the PR, delete the branch, switch to the main branch locally, and pull all changes. If the PR is already deployed, just switch to the main branch and pull the current changes for the main branch.

Delete the auxiliary md files that you used to create pr comments.

Never push direct changes to main branch! NEVER!
